ItemDescription.SourceString: A secured case containing essential equipment for operating the Committee's new monitoring system for the Pechorsk Anomaly and its entities. It can only be carried by hand.
A modernized weather sensor used by the Committee in the 1990s to monitor the Pechorsk Anomaly. It was phased out after the introduction of a new monitoring system.
A piece of common tableware from 1980s Pechorsk, recreated by the Radius in a distorted form. Studying it may shed light on the altering properties of the Pechorsk Anomaly.
A pantry container from 1980s Pechorsk, recreated by the Radius in a distorted form. Studying it may shed light on the altering properties of the Pechorsk Anomaly.
A simple tool from 1980s Pechorsk, recreated by the Radius in a distorted form. Studying it may shed light on the altering properties of the Pechorsk Anomaly.
A stinky soap bar from 1980s Pechorsk, recreated by the Radius in a distorted form. Studying it may shed light on the altering properties of the Pechorsk Anomaly.
A piece of flatware from 1980s Pechorsk, recreated by the Radius in a distorted form. Studying it may shed light on the altering properties of the Pechorsk Anomaly.
A wooden toy from 1980s Pechorsk, recreated by the Radius in a distorted form. Studying it may shed light on the altering properties of the Pechorsk Anomaly.
A rusty padlock from 1980s Pechorsk, recreated by the Radius in a distorted form. Studying it may shed light on the altering properties of the Pechorsk Anomaly.

A portable device that amplifies the signal in the Committee's sensor network, enhancing the accuracy of monitoring in harsh conditions. It aids in detecting unstable entities within the Pechorsk Anomaly.
A secured container for biological samples, used by the Committee to study the effects of the Pechorsk Anomaly's altering properties on blood and tissues of ordinary individuals.
